5|$|Archbishop Michael Peers {{apologized to}} {{residential}} school survivors, {{on behalf of}} the Anglican Church of Canada, on August 6, 1993, at the National Native Convocation in Minaki, Ontario. The following year the Presbyterian Church in Canada adopted <b>a</b> <b>confession</b> at its 120th General Assembly in Toronto on June 5, recognizing its role in residential schools and seeking forgiveness. The confession was presented on October 8 during a ceremony in Winnipeg.|$|E
